  <h1 class='post_title'>Fit Friends</h1>
  <a href='http://www.fit--friends.herokuapp.com'>www.fit--friends.herokuapp.com</a>
  <p class='post_info'>FitFriends keeps people motivated to exercise and stay healthy by enabling them to connect with their friends and achieve fitness goals as a community. Through the creation, completion, and sharing of challenges by its users, FitFriends transforms exercise from a personal adventure to a social one, motivating and exciting users to stay fit.
    <br><br>
  The application is heavy on the client side, utilizing JavaScript, JQuery, Ajax, and Handlebars, paired with a rails back-end that serves JSON. Our focus was to keep code clean and modular, enabling us to easily implement or remove functionality, to efficiently break up responsibilities, and to continue making adjustments and improvements into the future.
    <br><br>
  Having proposed the idea for this app, I was designated team lead. My responsibilities included managing the teams combined coding effort and ensuring we stayed on track to showcase a well built app with a tight deadline. My heaviest code contributions were in the friending and search functionalities, with additional support spread throughout the rest of the app.</p>
